      "lesson title": "Connected Vehicles and Expanding Attack Surfaces",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "Modern vehicles are no longer simply mechanical machines. They are increasingly connected devices that communicate with other vehicles, infrastructure, and cloud-based services, creating a vast and complex digital ecosystem. This lesson introduces the concept of attack surfaces and explores how the integration of IoT technologies and AI-driven systems into transport networks has significantly expanded the opportunities for cyber threats. You will learn how everyday features such as GPS navigation, remote diagnostics, and over-the-air software updates can introduce vulnerabilities if not properly secured. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of why cybersecurity is now a critical consideration for anyone working with or around connected transport systems.",
